The paper discusses biclustering, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining. The paper proposes two approaches for properly aggregating the whole set of enumerated biclusters, which is related to clustering and pattern recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DM (Data Mining), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
